Brazil defender, Maicon, has returned to Italy to continue his football career with Serie D side, Sona Calcio, Sky Sports reports. Maicon, 39, had been in talks with Sona Calcio before last year’s Christmas and the deal has now been finalized. His son, Felipe, 15, has also signed for Sona Calcio’s academy team. Maicon won the treble in 2009/2010 season with Inter Milan. The former Manchester City star also spent three seasons with AS Roma. “I am happy to be back in Italy with my son and I am excited for this new adventure as a player,” Maicon said after his arrival on Friday.